title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester Model 59
postcontent: I have for sale or trade a very nice Winchester Model 59, 12 gauge. The Model 59 is a lightweight version of the Model 50 with an aluminum receiver and "Winlite" barrel made from a thin steel tube wrapped in over 500 miles of fiberglass micro filament that was bonded and polished to look like blued steel. It has a 28" full choke barrel and weighs only 6.5lbs. The barrel itself only weighs about 12 ounces. These only have a 2 shot magazine tube as they were marketed towards bird hunters. The Model 50 and 59 utilize a short recoil action much like most centerfire autoloading pistols, designed by David Marshall "Carbine" Williams. The infamous moonshiner who developed the short stroke gas piston used in the M1 carbine. There is a floating chamber in the barrel which the bolt locks into, this chamber recoils for a short distance upon firing and then allows the bolt to unlock and cycle the action. Unlike gas operated shotguns that use the expanding gasses of the burnt powder to drive a piston, or the Browning long recoil system in which the entire barrel recoils upon firing. There's one tiny scratch on the left of the receiver only visible in bright light, very minor finish wear where the bolt handle rides in the receiver, and light handling marks on the wood. Overall I'd call it 95-98%. Only about 85,000 of these were made between 1960-1965 and it was Winchesters last hand built shotgun before they automated their plant. Asking $500 firm and I am open to trades. I've run about 3 boxes of light target loads through this gun and it functions flawlessly. I can provide more pictures on request.

Genuine CORE Rifle System Barrels begin with raw bar stock cut to length. We then drill the bar stock and button rifle the bar stock.
